   +pod('')
      .uk-width-medium-5-10
         p
            | Three-spine sticklebacks are small fish that live in oceans, streams, and lakes across the northern hemisphere. Sticklebacks that
            | live in freshwater lakes often look quite different from their ocean-dwelling cousins. One difference is the amount of protective
            | armor that covers their bodies: while oceanic sticklebacks have about 30 armor plates extending from head to tail, most freshwater
            | sticklebacks have just a handful of plates that sit closer to the front of the body.
      .uk-width-medium-5-10
         figure
